SUMMARY:National BBCB 2026 Summit
LOCATION:Tampa Convention Center 333 S Franklin St Tampa \, FL 33602 Unite
 d States
DESCRIPTION:For event details: web.cvent.com (https:web.cvent.comevent11f0
 56fc-3581-400e-853a-34859691a6a0summary) The 19th Annual National BBCB Sum
 mit will take place March 4-7\, 2026. Staying true to our mission\, BBCB  
 now known as: Believe. Build. Complete. Become.  remains deeply committed 
 to advancing college completion and paving a smoother path to student succ
 ess and has grown into a leading national event that is open to all studen
 ts of any background. After 19 years\, the Summit has been successful in a
 ttracting some of the most influential speakers and scholars to address ba
 rrier that affect persistence and completion among college students. A ser
 ies of theme-based workshops on contemporary provide an important focus to
  the Summit\, bringing together college students and practitioners to enga
 ge in dialogue about critical issues\, sharing successful strategies and b
 est practices. The 2026 Summit promises to be another exciting event featu
 ring Blair Underwood at the Dr. Sylvia Marion Carley luncheon\, with an ad
 ditional eight nationally acclaimed speakers including Damola Adamolekun\,
  Nigerian business executive and current chief executive officer of Red Lo
 bster Investor Holdings as well as Mark Dean\, former IBM computer enginee
 r whose most notable accomplishments include co-creating the IBM personal 
 computer released in 1981. Most importantly\, BBCB creates unique opportun
 ities and special student sessions for over 400 participants for over 150 
 educational institutions\, and 800 community members attend. \n\nPermalink
 : https://www.tampa.gov/node/178171
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/178171
END:VEVENT
